<doc id="983196" wikidata="Q52201" url="?curid=983196" title="Sternatia">
<text>Sternatia (Griko: , ) is a small town and &quot;comune&quot; in the province of Lecce, Apulia, southern Italy. It is one of the nine towns of Grecìa Salentina where the greek dialect Griko is spoken.

