<text>Corigliano d&#x27;Otranto (; ) is a small town and &quot;comune&quot; of 5,632 inhabitants in the province of Lecce in Apulia, Italy. It is one of the nine towns of Grecìa Salentina.
The inhabitants of Corigliano, alongside Italian, also speak Griko, a Greek dialect.


