<doc id="983400" wikidata="Q6460610" url="?curid=983400" title="L ring">
<text>The L-ring of the bacterial flagellum is the ring in the lipid outer cell membrane through which the axial filament (rod, hook, and flagellum) passes. that l ring stands for lipopolysaccharide.

